        <h2>Proposal</h2>
    </div>
    <p>
        The website will be an e-commerce platform for VUV Clothing, a clothing brand that sells different kinds of
        clothes. The website will allow customers to browse and purchase clothing items from the brand's collection. The
        website will also provide information about the brand, its products, and its mission.

    </p>
    <p>
        The website will sell a variety of clothing items, including tops, bottoms, dresses, skirts, jackets, and
        accessories. The website will also offer a variety of sizes and colors for each item.

    </p>
    <p>
        The clothing industry is a large and growing market. In the United States alone, the clothing industry is worth
        over $200 billion. The website will provide a convenient and affordable way for customers to purchase clothing
        from VUV Clothing.

    </p>
    <p>
        To meet the needs of our users, we will have different roles, including:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Admin:</strong> Manages the overall platform, sets policies, and oversees operations.</li>
        <li><strong>Customer:</strong> Shops for products, places orders, and tracks deliveries.</li>
        <li><strong>Seller:</strong> Lists products for sale, manages inventory, and tracks sales.</li>
        <li><strong>Developers:</strong> Responsible for developing new features in sites and maintain.</li>
        <li><strong>Graphic Designers:</strong> Responsible for creating the visual elements of the website, including
            logos, icons, and other graphical assets.</li>
        <li><strong>Customer Support Representatives:</strong> Responsible for providing assistance and support to
            website users, addressing any inquiries or issues they may have.</li>
        <li><strong>Marketing Specialist:</strong> Responsible for developing a marketing strategy for the website,
            including social media promotion, email marketing, and search engine advertising.</li>
        <li><strong>Content Writer:</strong> Responsible for creating engaging and relevant content for the website,
            including product descriptions, blog posts, and marketing copy.</li>
